data.description: MOVE-IN-READY – in FLOOD ZONE X - Stunning, 2017 built, spacious, immaculate, fully furnished 4 bedroom / DEN/Family/Flex Space / 2 bath, heated Pool Home located in the friendly Golfing Community of Rotonda. Relaxing should come naturally as you step in and see that there's nothing left to do but move into this turnkey furnished home and make it your own as the owner has just put on a new roof and rescreened the whole pool cage in 2023. There is room for everyone in this spacious home with a split floorplan and over 2300 square feet of living space with open design and high ceilings with tiles in living areas and carpet in all four bedrooms. This home lives large with multiple living spaces inside. A family room and dining area sets a nice impression once you enter the foyer boasting a nice view of the great room and the pool through the large glass sliding doors. The split floor plan with a separate master suite on one side of the home, three guest rooms with a bathroom on the other side, offers everyone plenty of privacy. This kitchen is decked out with beautiful cabinetry, granite countertops, stainless appliances, closet pantry and a bar complete with 6 barstools, ready to get the party started. Step outside through a set of sliding glass doors and entertain guests on the covered lanai overlooking the pool. Lanai comes with remote controlled Kevlar Shutters. The sparkling heated pool offers endless enjoyment day or night with its remote-controlled screen lights. At the end of the day, retreat to the generously sized master suite with his and her walk-in closets, en-suite bath with dual sinks, private lavatory, garden tub and separate shower.   The 8x6 ft laundry room comes with upper cabinets. There are shutters or accordion shutters for the whole house.    This beautiful home is located in Rotonda West which provides its homeowners with a beautiful 165 acre park, a new Community Center, five golf courses totaling 99 holes of fun and challenging play, tennis courts, pickleball courts, a playground, a pavilion, many lakes, abundant tropical landscape and wildlife with miles of biking and walking trails for the low HOA of $190 a year. Take a short car ride to the Gulf Beaches of Boca Grande, Palm Island, or Manasota Key to name a few where you will find world class fishing and sand between your toes. Other area amenities include boating, golfing, fine dining, and the Charlotte Sports Park welcoming the Tampa Bay Rays. Fly direct into several nearby international and regional airports offering a wide variety of destinations.    TV, love seat & clock in the great room, and the roll top desk in middle bedroom, and all personal items (clothiers, kitchen items, dishes & glasses, clothing and golf clubs) are not included. The beds, dressers, tables and other furniture is included.
